      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Cinthia" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Cinthia" href="/user/show/17081082-cinthia">Cinthia</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
                  <em>
                    This review has been hidden because it contains spoilers. To view it,
                    <a href="#" onclick="Effect.toggle(&#39;reviewTextContainer2574031606&#39;); return false;">click here.</a>
                  </em>
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2574031606" class="readable"
                    style="display:none"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16480404442403482229">I kept looking at this book on my shelf and dismissing it... finally I had to read it and let me tell you guys it was nice, the writing is excellent, easy to read and a lot more easier to get into. At first I didn&apos;t like Esperanza because she was so spoiled that she couldn&apos;t see beyond what she wanted and how her life was, she couldn&apos;t understand that after her fathers death they would have to start over if they wanted to be free from her uncles. I loved the Grandma she is so cool, passing down </span>
  <span id="freeText16480404442403482229" style="display:none">I kept looking at this book on my shelf and dismissing it... finally I had to read it and let me tell you guys it was nice, the writing is excellent, easy to read and a lot more easier to get into. At first I didn't like Esperanza because she was so spoiled that she couldn't see beyond what she wanted and how her life was, she couldn't understand that after her fathers death they would have to start over if they wanted to be free from her uncles. I loved the Grandma she is so cool, passing down her knowledge to Esperanza and later on to Isabel. Most of all I loved Ramona, Esperanza's mother, she was so strong and when she caught that valley fever I was so scared that she would not make it, she got pneumonia from the valley fever, it was just a mess, the conditions they had to live when they first came to America were terrible but there was always friends and work, I understood Marta's desire to strike for better working and living conditions and I am so proud of her but I also understand why Esperanza and the camp she was living in tried to stay out of it, it was a very difficult decision. Esperanza learned how to be a grown up way too quick when her mother fell ill and not being able to see her for months had taken a toll on her. I loved, loved Miguel! he called her "mi Reina" my queen. and when they fought he stole her money so he could go get her grandma ! that part almost killed me it was so endearing! I loved the story and being Spanish speaking I enjoyed the Spanish parts but was also glad that the author translated it for people that do not speak Spanish so it's easy to read and understand and not miss anything. I loved how hard Esperanza worked for those she loved, and those babies they sound so cute! I'm glad she gave Isabel the doll, the doll needed a girl that would love it and play with it. </span>
  <a data-text-id="16480404442403482229" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
